+# ArduPlane EKF3 ExternalNav without GPS
+
+This patch keeps Plane on EKF3 while feeding SITL NSU position and velocity
+directly into the EKF API. It does not use GPS, VisualOdom, `sim:vicon`, or
+MAVLink navigation messages, and does not implement IMU-only global navigation.
+
+## Configuration
+
+Use `Tools/autotest/default_params/plane-sitl-nsu-no-gps.parm`:
+
+```text
+AHRS_EKF_TYPE   3
+EK2_ENABLE      0
+EK3_ENABLE      1
+EK3_SRC1_POSXY  6
+EK3_SRC1_VELXY  6
+EK3_SRC1_POSZ   1
+EK3_SRC1_VELZ   6
+EK3_SRC1_YAW    1
+VISO_TYPE       0
+COMPASS_USE     1
+ARSPD_USE       1
+ARMING_CHECK    1
+RTL_AUTOLAND    3
+```
+
+Both GPS drivers and both SITL GPS sensors are disabled. The Plane-only SITL
+task provides horizontal position and three-axis velocity directly, the
+barometer provides height, the compass provides yaw, and airspeed plus ground
+velocity makes wind observable.
+
+Run the SITL aircraft as `--model plane-elevrev`, which is the ArduPlane
+autotest default. The plain `plane` model applies the opposite elevator sign
+for the default servo direction and causes unstable altitude feedback. The
+dedicated defaults use `INITIAL_MODE=0` and `FLTMODE_CH=0`, so Plane waits in
+the armable MANUAL mode before QGC uploads a mission and simulated RC input
+cannot silently replace a QGC-selected mode. Starting in AUTO without a mission
+would fall back to RTL, which Plane intentionally refuses to arm.
+`SIM_TERRAIN=0` keeps the runway flat at Home so the unbraked SITL model remains
+near its launch point while the operator plans the mission. A
+`SERVO3_MIN/TRIM/MAX` range of `1000/1000/2000` maps disarmed output to exactly
+zero thrust in the internal Plane model.
+The `plane-elevrev` profile also requires `RC2_REVERSED=1`, `RC4_REVERSED=1`,
+`SERVO2_REVERSED=1`, and `SERVO4_REVERSED=1`. These match the upstream
+ArduPlane autotest profile; omitting the elevator reversal turns a positive
+takeoff pitch request into a physical nose-down response.
+
+## Origin and Home
+
+Firmware sets EKF Origin and Home to the `--home` latitude, longitude, and AMSL
+altitude. No MAVLink initialization command is required.
+
+## Safety behavior
+
+All pre-arm checks remain enabled. A failed direct NSU feed must prevent arming.
+AUTO takeoff without GPS is accepted only while EKF reports healthy absolute
+horizontal position and velocity and is not in constant-position mode.
+
+QGC landing patterns contain `DO_LAND_START`. `RTL_AUTOLAND=3` allows this
+marker without changing normal RTL behavior; `RTL_AUTOLAND=0` must fail the
+mission pre-arm check.
+
+The QGC sequence is: wait for `Ready To Fly` in MANUAL, upload a mission that
+starts with TAKEOFF and ends with the landing pattern, select AUTO, then arm.
+
+Some QGC versions instantiate Copter/Rover failsafe Facts before applying the
+fixed-wing visibility rules. Plane SITL therefore exposes read-only
+`FS_OPTIONS`, `FS_GCS_TIMEOUT`, and `FS_GCS_ENABLE` compatibility Facts. They do
+not replace Plane's real `FS_GCS_ENABL` and `FS_LONG_TIMEOUT` behavior.
+
+## Test
+
+```sh
+../venv/bin/python Tools/autotest/autotest.py \
+  test.Plane.EKF3ExternalNavNoGPS --speedup=10
+```
+
+The test verifies internally initialized Origin/Home, checks direct NSU loss at
+pre-arm, takes off, maintains the commanded height, checks wind, completes an
+AUTO circuit, lands, and disarms.
